{
  "stem": "25773.6",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was-- that was a lovely time, because we walked among-- it was not-- somehow you didn't see a German.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Here and there, you saw the passing of motorcycles.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't bother about you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And apart from our sore feet, we work-- and sore hands-- we work in the fields.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We learned a lot how to-- you know, how to get the hay and-- and straw and God know what.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Than we had always a nice meal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And at one occasion, it was very, very funny because, you see, my friend comes from a very religious, Jewish home.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But she came from a very Orthodox home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one-- of one of the occasions, you were obliged to go to the-- obliged to go to the church, because, I mean, they-- they-- they thought-- I said to [?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Masia, ?] look.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We have to go to-- Krystyna goes to the church.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I will have to go to-- so she [INAUDIBLE], say I'm ill.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we did like that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Every time we said, she's ill.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I didn't mind to go to the church, because I always believe it's one God.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I believe in-- I admired, and I thought our ethics, our Jewish ethics, and our religion is-- is one.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We have given the Ten Commandments to the whole world, which is, up [? today ?] Romans and-- and-- and-- and the whole modern world took [? out a ?] [?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "God ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I believed in that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I was proud of being that, but I believe this one God.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it didn't matter whether I prayed in the church or whatever.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Masia ?] was always ill.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On one occasion, after the church was a big feast.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the-- the farmer's wife, one of the farmer's wife, made a big feast.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
